[In the absence of numbers, it is difficult to evaluate this situation. The persistence of mumps virus infection in a vaccinated, or perhaps partially vaccinated, population may be a reflection of the lesser immunising efficiency of the mumps component of the MMR (measles, mumps and rubella) triple vaccine. Further information would be appreciated regarding the prevalence of measles virus infection in this community, which might reveal gaps in immunisation coverage.

Palencia is the capital of the province of Palencia in the autonomous community of Castille and Leon, Spain. The Junta de Castilla y Leon is the governing body and administration of Castilla y Leon and exercises executive and regulatory power. The interactive ProMED/HealthMap of Palencia, Castille and Leon, Spain can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/49Km. - Mod.CP]
